# odio-api systemd reference — services exposed for this install.
#
# This file ships as `.default` and is ignored by odio-api. To override:
#
#   cp 10-systemd.yml.default 50-my-systemd.yml
#   $EDITOR 50-my-systemd.yml
#   systemctl --user restart odio-api
#
# odio-api merges every `conf.d/*.yml` on top of `config.yaml`, but the
# `system:` / `user:` arrays are replaced wholesale — your override must
# include every unit you want exposed, not just additions.
#
# Regenerated on each install.sh / odio-upgrade run; diff against your
# override to spot new defaults after an upgrade.

